League of American Theatres and Producers and the American Theatre Wing. This year, the duty of hosting the Tony Awards will be shared. The Tony Awards will be broadcast live from Radio City Music Hall on CBS, Sunday, June 11th, 8:00 - 11:00 p.m. (ET/PT time delay). The Tonys are presented by the League of American Theatres and Producers and the American Theatre Wing. At the League, Gerald Schoenfeld is Chairman and Jed Bernstein is President. At the Wing, Sondra Gilman is Chairman, Doug Leeds is President and Howard Sherman is Executive Director. For Tony Award Productions, Elizabeth I. McCann is Managing Producer and Joey Parnes is Coordinating Producer. Kirshner and Weiss/White Cherry Entertainment are Executive Producers of the 2006 Tony Awards. Weiss will also serve as Director of the 2006 Tony Awards. The official Tony Awards web site, www.TonyAwards.com , is developed, designed, and hosted by IBM, an official partner of the Tonys. Related Articles Comment & Share About Author Subscribe to Author Alerts Scroll Back To Top More Articles From Author Photo Flash: Inside Dramatists Guild of America's Annual Awards Ceremony with Stephen Schwartz, Christopher Durang & More Photo Flash Exclusive: David Goodman Visits Bryan Cranston at Broadway's ALL THE WAY Photo Flash: First Look at Audra McDonald as Billie Holiday in LADY DAY AT EMERSON'S BAR AND GRILL Artwork! Photo Flash: First Look at Beautiful Soup's LILIOM, Opening Tomorrow Photo Flash: Promo Shots for GET's THE GREAT GATSBY Animus Theatre Company's 2014 Season to Feature Matthew Lillard, Plays by Bob Glaudini, Tennessee Williams & More PLACAS with Ric Salinas to Run 4/3-6 at Los Angeles Theatre Center Profile Theatre Launches New Education Fund Magician John Tudor to Teach Children's Magic Workshop at CCT, 3/8 SHREK Opens at Playhouse Merced this Weekend BROADWAYWORLD TV STAGE TUBE: First Lady Michelle Obama Introduces THE TRIP TO BOUNTIFUL Screening STAGE TUBE: Lisa Howard Sings 'I Dreamed a Dream' at BROADW